  "prompt": "Who is best in Sachin, virat and dhoni?",
  "response": "That's the million-dollar question in Indian cricket! There's no single \"best\" \u2013 Sachin Tendulkar, Virat Kohli, and MS Dhoni are all legends who excelled in different ways and eras. Here's a breakdown to help you decide who *you* think is the \"best,\" keeping in mind it's ultimately subjective:\n\n**Sachin Tendulkar: The God of Cricket**\n\n*   **Batting Prowess:** Unparalleled. Holds almost every major batting record in both Tests and ODIs. Known for his incredible technique, consistency, and longevity.\n*   **Longevity:** Played international cricket for 24 years.\n*   **Impact:** Carried the hopes of a nation for decades. An inspiration to billions.\n*   **Stats (Highlights):**\n    *   Most Test runs: 15,921\n    *   Most ODI runs: 18,426\n    *   Most international centuries: 100\n*   **Weaknesses (relatively speaking):** Played in an era with arguably tougher bowling attacks on average. Wasn't known for his captaincy.\n\n**Virat Kohli: The Run Machine**\n\n*   **Batting Prowess:** Arguably the greatest ODI batsman of all time. Known for his aggression, fitness, and ability to chase down targets.\n*   **Aggression and Intensity:** Brings a high level of passion and intensity to the game.\n*   **Modern Era Dominance:** Dominated a significant portion of the modern game.\n*   **Stats (Highlights):**\n    *   Second-most ODI centuries: 50\n    *   Fastest to many milestone in ODI Cricket\n    *   One of the highest average in tests and ODI format\n*   **Weaknesses (relatively speaking):** His captaincy record in ICC tournaments is a point of debate. Has had periods of inconsistency.\n\n**MS Dhoni: Captain Cool and Finisher Extraordinaire**\n\n*   **Captaincy:** Arguably India's greatest captain. Led India to victory in the 2007 T20 World Cup, 2011 Cricket World Cup, and 2013 Champions Trophy (the only captain to achieve this).\n*   **Finishing Ability:** Renowned for his ability to stay calm under pressure and finish matches.\n*   **Wicket-Keeping:** Exceptional wicket-keeper with lightning-fast reflexes.\n*   **Stats (Highlights):**\n    *   Only captain to win all three major ICC trophies.\n    *   Holds numerous wicket-keeping records.\n    *   Known for his match-winning innings in pressure situations.\n*   **Weaknesses (relatively speaking):** His Test batting average is lower compared to Sachin and Virat. Relied more on power hitting than classical technique.\n\n**Here's a way to think about it:**\n\n*   **Best Batsman (Purely on Stats and Technique):** Sachin Tendulkar\n*   **Best ODI Batsman (Chasing and Impact):** Virat Kohli\n*   **Best Captain and Finisher:** MS Dhoni\n\n**Ultimately, the \"best\" is a matter of personal opinion.**  Consider what you value most in a cricketer:\n\n*   **Do you value sheer batting records and longevity?** Sachin might be your pick.\n*   **Do you value aggressive run-chasing and modern dominance?** Virat might be your pick.\n*   **Do you value captaincy, coolness under pressure, and finishing ability?** Dhoni might be your pick.\n\nThey all have contributed immensely to Indian cricket and are legends in their own right! You don't have to choose just one!\n",
